<br>
There has been so many suggestions as to how we should improve the caster classes importance. Increased mana pool, faster mana regen, harder nukes, faster nukes, more efficient nukes. All of these have side effects , most unbalancing ones. So they cannot be implemented..and shouldnt.<br>
<br>
The solution that suddenly popped into my head is this.<br>
The caster classes dont need any changes at all, what is needed to change is the way some NPCs behave in combat situations. As it is now every single mob in the game behaves the exact same way, it is attacked by you and immediately tries to get as close to you as possible and hit the living..out of you, perhaps casting a few nukes now and then. <br>
<br>
What is needed is this, mobs that instead of engaging the melee gets out of range from them and attacks with magic. The best solution for this would be a yonder type spell but with some degree more control than we have. This shouldnt be too hard to implement codewise as its just a trigger..when hit ..yonder to a certain distance and attack. It could possibly even aoe root or snare tanks to keep them away. What would this accomplish?<br>
<br>
Benefits<br>
<br>
1. It would be required that you have casters in your party that can attack it from a distance which make us wanted and needed. <br>
<br>
2. it does not take away the tanks importance at all since there will be normal mobs around as well of course. (as there are mobs now most casters cant even scratch ..these mobs will be hard for melee to harm). A way to be able to melee in these fights would be to stun the mob thus making the stun type spells very important.<br>
<br>
3. This would not unbalance the game in any way. These are certain types of situations in certain dungeons. <br>
<br>
4. There would be no need to implement super items with clarity, free super dds and so on for casters making us too powerful. (more on items later)<br>
<br>
5. As it is now the only caster classes that actually nuke are wizards and to a lesser degree mages. And its certainly only wizards that aoe. This would give every caster class a situation where it is encouraged and possibly needed for them to contribute to the dmg. Some would of course nuke more than others. Class specifics:<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Wizard: The purpose is clear..prime dmg dealer in these fights. DD and aoe and stun.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Magician: The air pet would be priceless with stuns of course, and they would DD and get &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp to aoe as they do have decent aoes.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Enchanter: Possible to mez everything and do the one target attack thing of course but thats &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp the boring and chicken way of doing it. Id like to see the enchanter being able to Nuke &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp more..aoe more (they do have some aoes dont they?)<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Druid: Dots are priceless, they can nuke, they can aoe, they can heal and certainly more.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Necromancer: Dots read above, nuke to some extent..i have never seen a necro aoe..can they?...mana dump! (boring but oh so&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp important in these fights)<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Shaman: Dots, nukes, heals, much resembling the druid role. And of course buffing as usual.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Paladin: Stun like crazy and possibly use that tiny little DD you have <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp who did i miss?<br>
<br>
6. An important thing about meelee vs caster equipment is that melees get better and better things improving their performance in battle to no end and casters see no noticable difference no matter what we get.(well some things does make a tiny difference). Suddenly with the mobs aggro always concentrated on you with magical attacks, your amount of resistances become extremely important. Instead of the AC melee have..you have resists. Thus making equipment necessary and greatly improving your gameplay in common (well more common than the once a month uberfight resists are really needed for now) fights and thus adding another dimension to caster equipment.<br>
<br>
7. Most of the mobs changed behavior shouldnt be too hard to program. Mobs already root..give them an aoe root or snare..mobs already gate..give them yonder.<br>
Mobs already stop to cast..make them stand still and cast longer. Mobs already run to a certain (minimum?) distance to you and bash your head in, make them run to a distance further from you and instead of melee, cast!<br>
One possible spell for them would be the proposed &quot;blink&quot; spell someone wanted wizards to have (an idea i pretty much like btw). A little yonder thats automatic when youre hit or going to be hit.<br>
<br>
Possible drawbacks.<br>
<br>
1. A mob yondering sounds like a nasty thing..it could yonder away into the middle of a group of other mobs, aggroing the whole bunch. Well that is for verant to prevent from happening too often <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  More controlled yonder spells would be of help.<br>
<br>
2. I honestly cant think of more drawbacks. I bet you can hehe<br>
<br>
Last but not least.. SCENARIO 1.<br>
<br>
Two groups of brave fighters enters the new and improved dungeon chardok for the first time. They have the normal group setups of mainly tanks , a cleric and chanter in each and an evacer (thats what we are sometimes<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> and a monk to pull. <br>
<br>
