<br>
Secondly, way to keep the interest with such a long post.<br>
<br>
Thirdly, the only thing I would see a problem with is the dungeon use vs. the ability for the PC caster to hit a target not in view.  A yonder would put them in another hallway which would nullify our effectiveness pretty well.  At least in many Sebi camps that would be the case.  We have a similar situation already with Mob Gating and Summoning.  However, in the current setup, once the mob gates and starts summoning, the group is finished if it can't camp out in time.  I would LOVE the idea of making situations where casters are actually a tool in the process and not an appliance for the cleanup.  Very nice post.<br>
